reviews.review: Very epic conclusion to the skywalker saga, lots of twists and turns I was not expecting. Iâ€™m a fan of this entire trilogy and what they did with it, and this final installment makes the entire series worth it in the end. My only complaint is that the beginning was very fast, but the entire movie was entertaining as hell.
Good movie, but y end the series??? Keep going!

This final trilogy started off strong and got worse as it went.  The Rise of Skywalker just made no sense.  Disney obviously did not have a cohesive story arc planned out and that's unfortunate.  Very disappointing.
I liked pretty much every single thing about the movie.  And I would pay to see the movie again and again.
I just feel like it was to much in this movie it is all coming to you at once and this should have been extended to at least a 3 hour movie. But other then that is was a great movie

In freudian terms Ryan Johnson had "slapped your grand mother" with his shameful take on ST, ie he inflicted pain to a beloved and defenseless figure for the sake of it. See how Luke was treated for instance. 
So for JJ to course correct like that and offer a loving action packed tribute brings closure to the saga. Sure it is not as mystical as the original story telling but its the best piece of entertainment I've seen in a long time.  Its
Visually gorgeous and the characters are treated with the love ans respect they deserve. Thank you JJ
Do not let the skeptics (critics) kill this movie, it's worth it and I went alone to see it taking a day off from work it was so good.

I liked this movie better than all of the other sequel trilogy movies. I think they did a good job of trying to fix mistakes that were made and introduce things that have never been in the movies before. It wasnt perfect but it was a lot of fun.  I liked that I felt like they restored hope to star wars and really tied everything together to end the entire story.
Great movie to end the Skywalker story!
